Definition: a law passed by the United States Congress that created the Occupational Safety and Health Administration to prevent employees from being injured or contracting diseases in the course of their employment
Synonyms: federal_job_safety_law, legislation, noun, group, law, c, a, passed, by, the, United, States, Congress, that, created, Occupational, Safety, and, Health, Administration, to, prevent, employees, from, being, injured, or, contracting, diseases, in, course, of, their, employment
Category: noun.communication
